===Etymology===
From {{etyl|NL.|en}} {{term|lithium|lang=la}}, from {{term|lithia|lang=la}} (in reference to Ancient Greek {{term|λίθος||stone|tr=lithos|lang=grc}}) + {{term|-ium|lang=la}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# {{uncountable}} The simplest [[alkali]] [[metal]], the lightest solid element, and the third lightest chemical element (''symbol'' Li) with an [[atomic number]] of 3.
# {{pharmaceutical drug|uncountable}} [[lithium carbonate|Lithium carbonate]] or other preparations of lithium metal used to treat [[manic depression]] and [[bipolar disorder]]s.
# A [[lithium battery]].

